02/11/2004
 SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Interior Minister Siljan Avramovski on Monday (1 November) refuted recent media speculation that alleged extremist groups are operating in the northern part of the country, posing new security threats. In a statement for the daily Dnevnik, Avramovski said that while there were some recent indications of criminal activity, police were taking the necessary measures. He ruled out the possibility of destabilisation.
In other news, Prime Minister Hari Kostov visits Germany on Tuesday to discuss Macedonia's Euro-Atlantic integration bid. (Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 02/11/04) 
